<http://identifiers.org/uniprot/P63208>
        a       owl:Class .

:R-HSA-5610785  a           obo:GO_0008150 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "In the absence of Hh signaling, the majority of full-length GLI3 is partially processed by the proteasome to a shorter form that serves as the principal repressor of Hh target genes (Wang et al, 2000). Processing depends on phosphorylation at 6 sites by PKA, which primes the protein for subsequent phosphorylation at adjacent sites by CK1 and GSK3. The hyperphosphorylated protein is then a direct target for betaTrCP-dependent ubiquitination and proteasome-dependent processing (Wang and Li, 2006; Tempe et al, 2006; Wen et al, 2010; Schrader et al, 2011; Pan and Wang, 2007)." ;
        rdfs:label          "GLI3 is processed to GLI3R by the proteasome" ;
        dc:contributor      "Authored: Rothfels, Karen, 2014-05-07" , "Reviewed: Liu, Yulu Cherry, 2014-08-01" , "Edited: Gillespie, Marc E, 2014-07-25" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-5610785" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-5610787/R-HSA-5610787> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

